    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/1071.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Ambassador</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: The Imperial Government has
                    instructed me to express to your excellency its special satisfaction at finding
                    the views concerning the American policy in the Far East, as set forth in your
                    excellency’s note of the 3d instant relative to China, to be in full consonance
                    with the German pursuits in China. Your excellency’s announcement appears to be
                    fully appreciated in Germany.</p>
                <p>Taking special pleasure in carrying out these instructions, I avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
